            <div type="general">
               <head>General</head>
               <p>Iksal is a small town in Lower Galilee situated in the Nazareth hills. The majority of its inhabitants are Arab Muslims. Historic evidence for it dates back to the Roman and Byzantine eras. The town inherits the remains of a castle probably built under Mamluk or Crusader rule.</p>
            </div>

            <div type="researchHistory">
               <head>Research history</head>
               <p><rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:8TTHJC3M">Palva (1965)</rs> is an investigation
               on anaptyctic and prothetic vowels in Lower Galilean Arabic, which also
               provides information on the dialect of Iksal and contains a collection of sample texts.</p>

               <p><rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:3EPF3B6L">Nevo (2006)</rs> presents a detailed linguistic description of the local Arabic.</p>
            </div>
